Daily Express crime correspondent John
Twomey, who is chairman of the Crime Reporters’ Association, said the 
NoW’s decision to use a surveillance team to follow police was 
‘shocking’.

The inquiry also heard that the Sunday
Mirror used counter-surveillance techniques when it interviewed one of 
the suspects in the case.

Mr Harrison said officers observed the
man being ‘picked up and driven round by a team that carried out 
anti-surveillance manoeuvres before dropping him off at a hotel to be 
interviewed’.

